what he 

00:06:39.786 --> 00:06:41.003
called the oversoul, "the 
silent, the universal beauty." 

00:06:41.004 --> 00:06:43.262
   Elizabeth Bishop's view of 
such 

00:06:46.531 --> 00:06:49.378
oneness, at least in her famous 
poem In the Waiting Room, is 

00:06:49.379 --> 00:06:51.379
less consoling.

00:06:55.480 --> 00:06:57.480
Suddenly, from inside came an 
owe of 

00:06:59.356 --> 00:07:01.356
pain, a voice, not very loud or 
long.

00:07:05.456 --> 00:07:07.899
I wasn't at all surprised. Even 
then I knew she was a foolish, 

00:07:08.513 --> 00:07:14.027
timid woman. I might have been 
embarrassed, but wasn't. What 

00:07:14.028 --> 00:07:16.028
took me completely by surprise 
was 

00:07:18.337 --> 00:07:20.999
that it was me, my voice and my 
mouth. Without thinking at all, 

00:07:21.000 --> 00:07:23.000
I was my foolish aunt.

00:07:27.139 --> 00:07:31.197
I, we, were falling, falling.
   One of poetry's great effects

00:07:31.198 --> 00:07:33.198
through its emphasis on feeling,
association, 

00:07:36.308 --> 00:07:38.308
music, and image, things we 
